<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="127" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="127">
Based on a description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Oberthuer, C" journalOrPublisher="Etudes de Lepidopterologie comparee" pageId="8" pageNumber="131" refId="B28" refString="Oberthuer, C, 1910. . Etudes de Lepidopterologie comparee 4" volume="4" year="1910">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Oberthür">Oberthuer</normalizedToken>
(1910
</bibRefCitation>
: 591), Verity provided the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verity" authorityYear="1920" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="subsp. pyrenaea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="pyrenaea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">pyrenaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the population of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1789" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhadamanthus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Zygaena rhadamanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurring at La Trancada 
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’Ambouilla">d'Ambouilla</normalizedToken>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pyrénées-Orientales">Pyrenees-Orientales</normalizedToken>
, between Prades and Mont Canigou). 
<bibRefCitation author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B20" refString="Leraut, P, 2012. Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids. NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 98) considered this taxon to be a 'simple 
<normalizedToken originalValue="synonym’">synonym'</normalizedToken>
of the nominotypical 
<taxonomicName authority="rhadamanthus" authorityName="rhadamanthus (Esper" authorityYear="1789" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. rhadamanthus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="rhadamanthus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Zygaena rhadamanthus rhadamanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a placement with which we agree even though 
<bibRefCitation author="Hofmann, A" journalOrPublisher="Harley Books, Colchester" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B17" refString="Hofmann, A, Tremewan, WG, 1996. A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae). Harley Books, Colchester" title="A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="1996">Hofmann and Tremewan (1996</bibRefCitation>
: 131) had considered it to be a valid subspecies with which the taxon 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aistleitner" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. boixolsis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="boixolsis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Zygaena rhadamanthus boixolsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Aistleitner, 1990, had been placed as a synonym. The latter is now automatically transferred as a synonym of the nominotypical subspecies. Specimens from La Trancada 
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’Ambouilla">d'Ambouilla</normalizedToken>
lack the white scaling (griseoid) on the ground colour of the forewings; moreover, a red abdominal cingulum is absent, as found in the nominotypical subspecies.
</paragraph>
